Create Staging Table 9

Steps to Create a Table in SQL Server Management Studio Using a Query

Click the Icon  on the left of the screen to download the source file needed to build this project.


Step 1: In the SQL Server Management Studio, click the New Query button on the toolbar

Step 2: Type or paste a CREATE TABLE script (example below)
Step 3: Click the Execute button on the toolbar

Note: Clicking the “New Query” button on the SSMS toolbar opens a new query. Clicking “Execute” runs the query.
